// ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// §2  PRODUCTION IMPLEMENTATIONS
// ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// What we have: Contracts and prototypes
// What we need: Production-quality implementations

// ── Complete Runtime Implementation ─────────────────────────────────────────

/*
Current state: Contract definitions + M1 prototypes
Needed: Full production runtime with:
- Mature garbage collector (not just RC + cycle collector)
- Advanced scheduler (preemption, priorities, fairness)
- Comprehensive syscall backends (all platforms)
- Production-grade FFI bridges
- Memory safety guarantees
- Exception safety
*/

// ── Compiler Backend Completion ─────────────────────────────────────────────

/*
Current state: Target-specific code generators (prototypes)
Needed:
- LLVM IR optimization passes
- Target-specific ABI compliance
- Link-time optimization
- Cross-compilation support
- Debug information generation
- Profile-guided optimization
*/

// ── Standard Library ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

/*
Massive gap: We have no standard library yet!

Needed:
- Collections (Vec, HashMap, BTreeMap, etc.)
- String manipulation and Unicode support
- I/O abstractions (files, networking, async I/O)
- Concurrency primitives (Mutex, RwLock, channels)
- Time and date handling
- Serialization (JSON, binary formats)
- Cryptography primitives
- OS abstractions
- Math libraries
- Testing framework
- Benchmarking utilities
*/

